difficult open question of whether Burau's matrix representation of the braid group is faithful. Chapter 4 is a broad view of recent results on the connections between braid groups and mapping class groups of surfaces. Chapter 5 contains a brief discussion of the theory of "plats." Research problems are included in an appendix.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 0aBraid theory. 0aKnot theory. 0aRepresentations of groups. 7aMATHEMATICS / Topology.2bisacsh  aAddition.  aAlexander polynomial.  aAlgebraic structure.  aAutomorphism.  aBall (mathematics).  aBijection.  aBraid group.  aBraid theory.  aBranched covering.  aBurau representation.  aCalculation.  aCartesian coordinate system.  aCharacterization (mathematics).  aCoefficient.  aCombinatorial group theory.  aCommutative property.  aCommutator subgroup.  aConfiguration space.  aConjugacy class.  aCorollary.  aCovering space.  aDehn twist.  aDeterminant.  aDiagram (category theory).  aDimension.  aDisjoint union.  aDouble coset.  aEigenvalues and eigenvectors.  aEnumeration.  aEquation.  aEquivalence class.  aExact sequence.  aExistential quantification.  aFaithful representation.  aFinite set.  aFree abelian group.  aFree group.  aFundamental group.  aGeometry.  aGroup (mathematics).  aGroup ring.  aGroupoid.  aHandlebody.  aHeegaard splitting.  aHomeomorphism.  aHomomorphism.  aHomotopy group.  aHomotopy.  aIdentity element.  aIdentity matrix.  aInclusion map.  aInitial point.  aInteger matrix.  aInteger.  aKnot polynomial.  aKnot theory.  aLens space.  aLine segment.  aLine–line intersection.  aLink group.  aLow-dimensional topology.  aMapping class group.  aMathematical induction.  aMathematics.  aMatrix group.  aMatrix representatio